:'''New Prison Guard:''' Wait, did you take that book ''A Study into the Mara-Struck'' with you just now?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Yes, I love to read to widen my knowledge.
:::'''New Prison Guard:''' It's got nothing to do with whether you like to read or not. You are helping it to escape from jail!
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Didn't you place it there for me to take...?
:::'''New Prison Guard:''' For you to take? No way. You are helping it to escape the prison!
::'''New Prison Guard:''' I've only recently been assigned to this section of The Shackling Prison, so I'm uncertain about this book's circumstances. However, judging from my experiences, it's likely here for a reason.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} Are you serious? Are you sure this isn't a joke?
:::'''New Prison Guard:''' I was hired as a Jailer in the Ten-Lords Commission because my personality is always serious. In my opinion, this book must have done something wrong and been arrested.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} So that's the reason no one can find this book...
:::'''New Prison Guard:''' ...Is anyone searching for this book? Please inform them that this book has been apprehended, which is why it's not readily available. My apologies for any inconvenience.
::'''New Prison Guard:''' In any circumstance, the Ten-Lords Commission will not make a mistake. We will never mistreat a good book.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} But what exactly is the charge?
:::'''New Prison Guard:''' ...Anyone without a charge will not be in prison. You're right. Let me do a quick check now.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} I got it. I will leave this book behind.
:::'''New Prison Guard:''' All right. Then I'll... On what charge should I rearrest it? Let me do a quick check.
::'''New Prison Guard:''' This is weird. There isn't any record in the system. Could it be that it's not a criminal?
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} That is more in line with my common sense...
:::'''New Prison Guard:''' You are right. You may bring the book along with you.
::{{DIcon|Arrow}} So I can take it with me now?
:::'''New Prison Guard:''' Yes, you may take the book with you...
::'''New Prison Guard:''' I've got duties to attend to and need to get back on patrol. If you are curious about why the ''A Study into the Mara-Struck'' book is locked up in prison, you can seek out Jailer Chiyi for further information.
::You finally get your hands on the '''unfindable ''A Study into the Mara-Struck'''''. If only there were a global channel, you would tell everyone in the Cosmos who's trying to find this book.
::But it's just an ordinary book, intriguing in its content but hardly worth breaking into the Shackling Prison for... This only deepens the mystery &mdash; who took this book away? And for what reason was it confined within the shadows of the Shackling Prison, hidden from the world's view?
::Perhaps finding the answer to this question will not give you a real sense of accomplishment, but having an unsolved puzzle in your mind makes you uneasy. Just as the new prison guard has suggested, it's time to look for Chiyi.
